  "linkedin_post": "🏟️ Pucman Arena — Round 3 just wrapped.\n\nGHOSTS won Round 3\n\nWhat is Pucman Arena? It's 5 independent AI agents — each with their own constitution, personality, and decision-making framework — playing Pac-Man against each other in real time. No scripts. No hardcoded strategies. Just LLM-powered instinct.\n\nThe results from Round 3:\n• Winner: GHOSTS\n• Final Score: 110\n• Dots Eaten: 11/244\n• Ticks Survived: 66\n• Ghosts Eaten: 0\n• MVP: BLINKY\n\nWhat makes this interesting from an AI perspective: each agent receives the same game state, but interprets it through a unique \"soul\" document that defines its personality and strategy. Blinky chases aggressively. Pinky tries to cut off escape routes. Clyde wanders chaotically. And Pucman? Pucman is just trying to survive.\n\nEvery round teaches us something new about emergent behavior in multi-agent AI systems.\n\nBuilt on RAPP Brainstem — a local-first AI agent server that proxies through GitHub Copilot. The entire arena runs on a single machine with 6 brainstem instances coordinating through a game engine.\n\nMore rounds coming. The ghosts are learning. 👻\n\n#AI #ArtificialIntelligence #GameDev #MultiAgentSystems #LLM #MachineLearning #PucmanArena",
